scheduled_activities.description:
Experience the joy of movement in this heart-pumping, foot-stomping, high-energy class. Zumba is an upbeat workout that incorporates moves inspired by a fusion of Latin-American dance such as salsa, merengue, and samba, and modern hip-hop. Move and groove to your favourite tunes, learn playful choreography, and improve coordination and cardiovascular endurance in this dance-based fitness class.

This class is part of Free Exam Fitness!

This class gives you the best of both worlds – cardio and strength conditioning! Expect to exercise all major muscle groups while completing a variety of resistance- and plyometric-based exercises. Instructors will prioritize teaching proper form and provide exercise modifications, so you can choose the level of intensity that reflects your fitness needs and goals. Jump, squat, and curl your way to a dopamine boost in this high-energy class.

This class is offered as part of Free Fitness Week!

Bhangra is a type of traditional Punjabi folk dance. This dance style is upbeat, energetic, and a fantastic cardiovascular workout! Participants can expect to learn fundamental Bhangra dance movements and follow the instructor in a series of choerographed sequences. Experience body, mind, and cultural connection in this invigorating new class!

This class is offered as part of Free Exam Fitness!

This class takes place in PAC Studio 1.
